						<summary>

						<p>North wall of the Tiruttaḷīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Kṛishṇarāya Śaka 1432 = 1510 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>The details of date of the record viz., Śaka 1432, Pramōdūkā, Uttarāyaṇa, Vasanta-ṛitu, Ṛishabha śu 12, Monday, Svāti-nakshatra regularly correspond to 1510 A.D., May 20.</p>						

						<p>It seems to state that Śiṅgama-nāyakkar, son of Veṅgala-nāyakkar of Sinda-ppaṭṭu ratified a grant of 6 <hi rend="italic">mā</hi> of land previously made by Bhairavanayiṉār, son of Dakshiṇāmūrti-bhaṭṭar Ādityadēvar of Kāñchīpuram belonging to Bhārgava-gōtra and Bōdhāyana-sūtra, for the merit of <hi rend="italic">Svāmi</hi> Chellappar <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Vīra Narasiṁharāya-nāyakkar and the same land was made over as <hi rend="italic">sarvamānya</hi> to a person who was the son of Śrīsthalīśa-bhaṭṭa, belonging to Prathama Ātrēya-gōtra and Āgnēya vaiśya-sūtra and residing at Tirupputtūr, a <hi rend="italic">brahmadēya</hi> in Kēraḷaśiṅga-vaḷanāḍu, for the enjoyment of his heirs. The chief who ratified this grant, is described with a string of <hi rend="italic">birudas</hi> like <hi rend="italic">gaṇḍara-gaṇḍa, Vaidigajabhīma,</hi> etc., probably indicating a high rank during the rule of this king.</p>						

						</summary>
